Edo State governor Mr Godwin Obaseki, yesterday, said his administration has put in place a development blueprint that would transform the state and make it more economically viable than Lagos state. Obaseki who spoke at a Town Hall meeting of Edo people in Lagos State with the theme: “Edo Okpa no”, said he is focused on taking the state to the next level and not bothered about his re-election , saying,” my re-election is a settled matter”. The governor added that,” we are thinking of the next generation, where will Edo be in year 2050 ? How would we reposition by 2050, how do we overtake Lagos by 2050? And it is possible. If Lagos can why not, it’s not about competition, we are sister states and will cooperate. All we need to do is to plan, because those who fail to plan are equally planning to fail. It’s about rigorous planning. ” Obaseki said economic development has been the focus of his administration since 2016, by adopting a strategic approach in promoting private enterprise, improving business environment, encouraging investments and rebuilding critical infrastructure. The governor explained that the government has succeeded in improving the quality of Education in the state, by getting I’d right at the basic level. He said the place of quality education cannot be over emphasized, saying it’s is getting quality education that would make people useful to the society. The governor said, “The priority is the basic education , the first six nine years a child should learn. Because if a child have not been taught to spell properly the child will not be able to develop other skills.” According to him, he has been able to improve the productivity of workers through training of workers and creation of positive work environment through refurbished of workspace. He added that strategic plan to revamp the health sector commenced in the state with focus on primary health care, human capital and infrastructure development in the health institutions.